paragraphs: The AAU Libraries offer students and faculty extensive access to top electronic resources, journals, and research tools through partnerships with leading publishers like Elsevier and Wiley. Collaborations with EIFL and the Ministry of Education also provide article processing charge (APC) waivers and discounts to support Ethiopian researchers.

With branches across 10 colleges, the AAU Library system is a central resource for academic support across diverse disciplines. As a member of the Consortium of Ethiopian Academic and Research Libraries (CEARL), it contributes to a broader network aimed at enriching research infrastructure throughout Ethiopia, equipping scholars with vital resources to drive academic and scientific advancement in the nation.

paragraphs: The Addis Ababa University Book Center, founded in 1984 G.C., has played a crucial role in supporting academic growth and providing essential resources to the university community. Over the years, it has grown into a vital hub for educational publications, stationery, and other services.

The University Book Center is the official bookshop for the entire Addis Ababa University. The Center boasts a large selection of textbooks, reference materials, monographs, journals. Also available are general-interest books, literature, technical books, and best sellers for customers from within and outside of AAU. The range of books, many of them published by the AAU Press, covers virtually all fields by Ethiopian and foreign authors. The book center also sells a broad array of other educational and office stationery supplies, and related items.
